Claims Claims: 1 . A method comprising: - encoding a first scalability layer comprising at least a first coded picture, the first scalability layer being an independent layer; - reconstructing the first coded picture into a first reconstructed picture; - encoding a second coded picture on a second scalability layer, wherein said encoding comprises: o reconstructing a second reconstructed picture by resampling at least a part of the first reconstructed picture; o indicating that one of the following is used as a reference for the second coded picture: the first coded picture or the first reconstructed picture; and that no prediction error is present in the second coded picture; - encoding a third coded picture on a third scalability layer, the third scalability layer representing a different view or view direction than the first scalability layer, wherein said encoding comprises: o using the second reconstructed picture as a reference for one or more of the following: inter-view sample prediction, inter-view motion prediction for the third coded picture. 2. The method according to claim 1 , further comprising: - indicating that the second scalability layer conforms to a second profile; and - indicating that the third scalability layer conforms to a third profile, wherein the third profile differs from the second profile. 3. An apparatus comprising at least one processor, memory including computer program code, the memory and the computer program code configured to, with the at least one processor, cause the apparatus to perform at least the following: - encode a first scalability layer comprising at least a first coded picture, the first scalability layer being an independent layer; - reconstruct the first coded picture into a first reconstructed picture; - encode a second coded picture on a second scalability layer, wherein said encoding comprises: o reconstructing a second reconstructed picture by resampling at least a part of the first reconstructed picture; o indicating that one of the following is used as a reference for the second coded picture: the first coded picture or the first reconstructed picture; and that no prediction error is present in the second coded picture; 

 - encode a third coded picture on a third scalability layer, the third scalability layer representing a different view or view direction than the first scalability layer, wherein said encoding comprises: o using the second reconstructed picture as a reference for one or more of the following: inter-view sample prediction, inter-view motion prediction for the third coded picture. 4. A computer program product embodied on a non-transitory computer readable medium, comprising computer program code configured to, when executed on at least one processor, cause an apparatus or a system to implement a method according to any of the preceding claims 1 to 2. 5. A method comprising: - decoding a first scalability layer comprising at least a first coded picture, the first scalability layer being an independent layer; - determining the first coded picture from a first reconstructed picture; - decoding a second coded picture on a second scalability layer, wherein said decoding comprises: o reconstructing a second reconstructed picture by resampling at least a part of the first reconstructed picture; o decoding an indication that one of the following is used as a reference for the second coded picture: the first coded picture or the first reconstructed picture; and that no prediction error is present in the second coded picture; - decoding a third coded picture on a third scalability layer, the third scalability layer representing a different view or view direction than the first scalability layer, wherein said decoding comprises: o using the second reconstructed picture as a reference for one or more of the following: inter-view sample prediction, inter-view motion prediction for the third coded picture. 6. An apparatus comprising at least one processor, memory including computer program code, the memory and the computer program code configured to, with the at least one processor, cause the apparatus to perform at least the following: - decode a first scalability layer comprising at least a first coded picture, the first scalability layer being an independent layer; - determine the first coded picture from a first reconstructed picture; - decode a second coded picture on a second scalability layer, wherein said decoding comprises: 

 o reconstructing a second reconstructed picture by resampling at least a part of the first reconstructed picture; o decoding an indication that one of the following is used as a reference for the second coded picture: the first coded picture or the first reconstructed picture; and that no prediction error is present in the second coded picture; - decode a third coded picture on a third scalability layer, the third scalability layer representing a different view or view direction than the first scalability layer, wherein said decoding comprises: o using the second reconstructed picture as a reference for one or more of the following: inter-view sample prediction, inter-view motion prediction for the third coded picture. 7. A computer program product embodied on a non-transitory computer readable medium, comprising computer program code configured to, when executed on at least one processor, cause an apparatus or a system to implement a method according to claim 5. 8. A method comprising: - obtaining a first set of scalability layers jointly covering a broadest displayable field-of-view, and obtaining a second set of scalability layers, the first set being independently decodable of the second set, and the second set enhancing the quality, resolution or other properties compared to the first set; - generating a media presentation description on the first set and the second set; - generating one or more media segments from the first set and the second set; - providing, in the media presentation description, one or more first indications of a field-of-view covered by the first set; - providing, in at least one of the media presentation description and the media segments, one or more second indications for enabling to request the reception of the first set separately from the second set; - providing, in at least one of the media presentation description and the media segments, one or more third indications for enabling to request the reception of a first subset of the second set separately from a second subset of the second set, the first subset representing a different view direction than the second subset, and the first subset and second subset being independently decodable from each other. 9. A server device comprising at least one processor, memory including computer program code, the memory and the computer program code configured to, with the at least one processor, cause the apparatus to perform at least the following: - obtain a first set of scalability layers jointly covering a broadest displayable field-of-view, and obtaining a second set of scalability layers, the first set being independently decodable of the second set, and the second set enhancing the quality, resolution or other properties compared to the first set; - generate a media presentation description on the first set and the second set; - generate one or more media segments from the first set and the second set; - provide, in the media presentation description, one or more first indications of a field-of-view covered by the first set; - provide, in at least one of the media presentation description and the media segments, one or more second indications for enabling to request the reception of the first set separately from the second set; - provide, in at least one of the media presentation description and the media segments, one or more third indications for enabling to request the reception of a first subset of the second set separately from a second subset of the second set, the first subset representing a different view direction than the second subset, and the first subset and second subset being independently decodable from each other. 10. A computer program product embodied on a non-transitory computer readable medium, comprising computer program code configured to, when executed on at least one processor, cause a server device to implement a method according to claim 8. 1 1 . A method comprising: - parsing from a media presentation description o that a first set of scalability layers and a second set of scalability layers are available from a server; and o the first set is independently decodable of the second set; and o the second set enhances the quality, resolution or other properties compared to the first set; - parsing, from the media presentation description, one or more first indications of a field-of-view covered by the first set; - determining to receive the first set of scalability layers on the basis of the field-of-view; 

 - parsing, from at least one of the media presentation description and media segments, one or more second indications for enabling to request the reception of the first set separately from the second set; - requesting coded data of the first set from the server; - parsing, from at least one of the media presentation description and the media segments, one or more third indications for enabling to request the reception of a first subset of the second set separately from a second subset of the second set, the first subset representing a different view direction than the second subset, and the first subset and second subset being independently decodable from each other; - requesting coded data of the first subset or the second subset from the server, based on a view direction to be displayed. 12. A client device comprising at least one processor, memory including computer program code, the memory and the computer program code configured to, with the at least one processor, cause the apparatus to perform at least the following: - parse from a media presentation description o that a first set of scalability layers and a second set of scalability layers are available from a server; and o the first set is independently decodable of the second set; and o the second set enhances the quality, resolution or other properties compared to the first set; - parse, from the media presentation description, one or more first indications of a field-of-view covered by the first set; - determine to receive the first set of scalability layers on the basis of the field- of-view; - parse, from at least one of the media presentation description and media segments, one or more second indications for enabling to request the reception of the first set separately from the second set; - request coded data of the first set from the server; - parse, from at least one of the media presentation description and the media segments, one or more third indications for enabling to request the reception of a first subset of the second set separately from a second subset of the second set, the first subset representing a different view direction than the second subset, and the first subset and second subset being independently decodable from each other; - request coded data of the first subset or the second subset from the server, based on a view direction to be displayed. 13. A computer program product embodied on a non-transitory computer readable medium, comprising computer program code configured to, when executed on at least one processor, cause a server device to implement a method according to claim 1 1 .
